We recommended and Management agreed to require the Municipal Accountant to:
a. Record the loan proceeds by debiting Cash in Bank – LCCA (1-01-02-010) and credit the Loans Payable- Domestic account (2-01-02-040);
b. Recognize in the Trust Fund accounts the transfer of funds from the 20% Development Fund by debiting Cash in Bank – LCCA (1-01-02-010) and credit the Due to Other Funds (2-03-01-010);
c. Recognize the accrued interest expense (5-03-01-020) on the loans as of December 31, 2023;
d. Recognize the earned interest income (4-02-02-220) on the bank accounts ending 4031 and 4531 as of December 31, 2023; and
e. Recognize the acquisition of Motor Grader, Hydraulic Excavator, and Vibratory Compactor in the Construction and Heavy Equipment account (1-07-05-080).

We recommended and Management agreed to require the BAC to:
a. Contracts thru Public Bidding:
   i. Submit the following:
      i. Certified copies of invitation to observers and evidence of receipt;
      ii. Copies of the Notice of Award and Notice to Proceed posted in the PhilGEPS website, the website of Procuring Entity, if any, and in the premises of the Procuring;
      iii. Proof of warranty security required;
      iv. Submit the perfected PO/Contracts within the prescribed period;
b. Procurement thru Small Value Procurement:
   a. Include in the APP the planned purchases of goods/supplies intended in the succeeding year as supported by the PPMP;
   b. For procurement worth more than ₱50,000.00, copies of Request for Quotation as posted in PhilGEPS;
   c. Abstracts of Quotation;
   d. Documentary requirements supporting supplier’s evaluation such as Mayor’s Permit, PHILGEPs Registration, Income/Business Tax Return, and Omnibus Sworn Statement;
   e. Avoid purchasing pharmaceuticals and medicines with brand names. Instead, utilize general phrases or names in all transactions involving the purchase of the same.
c. Procurement thru Shopping:
   a. Ascertain that the mode of procurement of common supplies/goods be reflected in the APP;
   b. Submit the following:
      a. BAC resolution justifying the change in mode of procurement from Small Value Procurement to Shopping;
      b. For procurement worth more than ₱50,000.00, copies of Request for Quotation as posted in PhilGEPS;
      c. Abstract of Quotation;
      d. The required Documentary Requirements per Appendix A of the same Annex H, particularly, Mayor’s Permit, PhilGEPS Registration, Income/Business Tax Return, and Omnibus Sworn Statement of suppliers;
d. Procured goods/supplies by reimbursement:
   a. To immediately stop the practice of cash payments to suppliers of goods and materials as this is not among alternative modes authorized and to issue checks directly to suppliers with the tax already withheld;

We recommended and Management agreed to:
a. Require the DO to submit liquidation voucher complete with supporting documents to include an attendance sheets, and food costing reports to the Accountant;
b. Require the Accountant to stop processing additional cash advances unless the previous cash advances have been fully liquidated;
c. Ascertain that cash advances are actually liquidated by the DCWs and that no funds remain at the end of the feeding periods;
d. Avoid the consolidation of liquidating individual acknowledgement/temporary receipts in a single RER and observe the limitation of ₱1,000.00 ceiling for RER;
e. Observe strictly the procurement process through Negotiated Procurement-Community Participation and establish local sources; and
f. Open a separate and distinct bank account for the SFP.

We recommended and Management agreed to:
a. Strengthen monitoring activities and come-up with realistic/doable project implementation schedule; and
b. Streamline planning and procurement activities of all infrastructure related PPAs to fast-track project implementation of all on-going/ not started PPAs;

We recommended and Management agreed to:

Require the Supply/Property Officer to:

Prepare an updated list of all PPE items costing ₱15,000.00 and above;

Prepare/update Property Cards for all PPE items reported as of December 31, 2022;

Prepare the Inventory and Inspection Report of Unserviceable Property (IIRUP) for all obsolete or unserviceable PPEs.

Reconcile property records with the Accounting Unit;

Submit to the Inventory Committee the updated list as basis in the preparation of working papers for the physical inventory taking activities.

b) Likewise, direct the Accounting Unit to:

Update/prepare PPELCs for all PPE items per Accounting records; 

Ensure that updated PPELCs reconcile with the controlling PPE General Ledger accounts; and

Reconcile PPELC with the property cards of the Property Unit.

We recommended and Management agreed to require the:

The Municipal Accountant to:

Record purchases of supplies and materials for stock to their appropriate inventory accounts;

Maintain the necessary perpetual inventory records in accordance with Section 114 of the New Government Accounting System for Local Government Units, Volume I; and

Record stock issuances only upon submission of SSMI with original copy of the RIS pursuant to Sec. 121 of NGAS, Vol. 1;

The Supply Officer to:

Consolidate weekly the RIS for which supplies and materials were issued using the SSMI and submit the same, with the RIS, to the Accountant for recording of the cost of supplies and materials issued; 

Prepare and submit to the Municipal Account the Summary of Supplies and Materials Issued (SSMI) immediately, with supporting Requisition and Issue Slips; and

Conduct a semestral physical count of inventory items by type and submit the results to the Inventory Committee.

We recommended and Management agreed to require the BAC and the BAC Secretariat to:

a. Indicate the mode of procurement, Public Bidding or other Alternative Mode of Procurement, in the APP;			

b. 	Submit the Minutes of the Pre-bid Conference for the Construction of the Slaughterhouse and Improvement of the Public Market (Phase IV);

c. 	Submit the eligibility checklist, in all bid evaluations, to ascertain the completeness of submitted documents;				
			d. 	Submit the Bid Security or Bid Securing Declaration of winning bidders for all public bidding conducted; 

e. 	Notify the bidders of the bids received by the BAC within seven days from the date of bid opening;				
			f. 	Post the Notice of Award, CA/PO, and Notice to Proceed in the PhilGEPS and the website of the Procuring Entity within the prescribed period; 						
			g. 	Submit the Performance Security of the bidders who were issued with the Notice of Award as listed in Observation Number 7 above.

h. 	 Execute only one CA/PO based on the terms and conditions as what was posted in the PhilGEPS;

i. 	Describe “The Works” contained in the Contract Agreement (CA) consistent with what is indicated in the Invitation to Bid.

We recommended and Management agreed to require the Bids and Awards Committee to:

a. 	Consolidate all requisitions for supplies and equipment of similar items quarterly and procure them through public bidding;  

b. 	Stop employing Shopping, as an alternative mode of procurement, for the purchase of materials for road rehabilitation/concreting as Shopping covers only ordinary or regular office supplies and equipment necessary in the transaction of its official business, and consumed in the day-to-day office operations (Item V.C (b) of Annex “H” of the IRR of RA 9184);

c. 	Consolidate in the APP all procurement activities contained in the verified PPMP submitted by the LDRRMO thru the Budget Officer and indicate the mode of procurement to use; 

d. 	Procure only materials indicated in the approved APP pursuant to Item 7.2 of the IRR of RA 9184;


e. 	Henceforth, strictly comply with Sections 10 and 48.2 of the Revised 2016         IRR of R.A. No. 9184, and Section 26 of COA Circular No. 92-386 dated          October 20, 1992.

We recommended and Management agreed to require the Disaster Risk Reduction Management Officer (DRRMO) to:

Plan judiciously all procurement activities consistent with the approved budget of the DRRM Office and PPAs funded by the LDRRMF pursuant to Section 7.1 of the IRR of RA 9184;

Prepare the Project Procurement Management Plan (PPMP) to contain all procurement activities to undertake for the budget year, indicating the procurement methods to be adopted, pursuant to Section 7.3.2 of the IRR of RA 9184;

Submit to the Budget Officer the PPMP to ensure consistency with the office’s budget proposal;


Require the Bids and Awards Committee to:

Consolidate in the APP all procurement activities contained in the verified PPMP submitted by the LDRRMO thru the Budget Officer and indicate the mode of procurement to use; 

Procure infrastructure projects, goods/supplies, and materials indicated in the approved APP pursuant to Item 7.2 of the IRR of RA 9184;

Submit the Bid Securing declaration for the procurement of materials for the construction of the Hanging Bridge in Brgy. Guintas with a contract price of 457,339.00;

Notify bidders of the bids received   within 7 calendar days to ensure transparency and accurate representation of the bid submission in accordance with Sec 25.7 of the IRR;

Post in the PhilGEPS or the website of the agency the Notice of Award, Purchase Order/Contract, and Notice to Proceed pursuant to related provisions of the IRR of RA 9184; 

Ensure that the “The Works” as described in the CA is consistent with what has been advertised per Invitation to Bid;

Use the RFQ and Abstract of Quotations instead of canvass forms to request price quotations, and Abstract of Canvass in accordance with 3 (a-c, e) of GPPB Resolution No. 09-2009 dated November 23, 2009, on the Guidelines for Shopping and Small Value Procurement;

Post the RFQs on the PhilGEPS website and the website of the agency for projects with an Approved Budget for the Contract above ₱50,000.00 in accordance with Item E of the same Annex H;

Attach the required Documentary Requirements per Appendix A of the same Annex H, particularly, Mayor’s Permit, PhilGEPS Registration, Income/Business Tax Return, and Omnibus Sworn Statement of suppliers.

Oversee the preparation of the Abstract of Quotations instead of Abstract of Canvass.

